Statistical analyses were performed using Prism 5.0 software package (Prism Software, Irvine, CA, USA). Normality of the data was demonstrated using a Kolmogorov-Smirnoff test. Paired t-tests were used to evaluate differences in mean values of cytokines levels, considering the comparative analysis of T0 and T3 (Fig. 1
) or T90 (Fig. 2
) or T885 (Fig. 3
), in each group evaluated. Unpaired t-tests were used to evaluate differences in mean of values of TGF-β (Table 1
). Analysis of variance (ANOVA) test followed by Tukey's multiple comparisons were used in the evaluation between the different treatment groups for cytokines (Fig. 1, Fig. 2, Fig. 3) and nitric oxide (Fig. 4
) analysis. Differences were considered significant when P values were <0.05.
